#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-SM-18-039.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

The diagram shows the state of stress that exists at a point in a machine component made of mild steel. Using both the von Mises yield criterion for ductile metals and the Tresca yield criterion, determine the most tensile and the most compressive transverse stress [`\sigma_z`] that can be applied before yielding occurs. For this grade of steel [`\sigma_z = [$y]`] [`ksi`].

Most compressive [`\sigma_z`]:  
[`\sigma_{Mises}=`] [____]{"$cmises"} [`ksi`]  
[`\sigma_{Tresca}=`] [____]{"$ctresca"} [`ksi`]  

Most tensile [`\sigma_z`]:  
[`\sigma_{Mises}=`] [____]{"$tmises"} [`ksi`]  
[`\sigma_{Tresca}=`] [____]{"$ttresca"} [`ksi`]  

END_PGML

